# Hyper-V Enhanced Session for Ubuntu (XRDP + XFCE)

Reliable Hyper-V Enhanced Session setup for Ubuntu virtual machines using:

- XRDP
- XFCE desktop
- Hyper-V vsock transport
- Dynamic resolution
- Clipboard support

## Why this project exists

GNOME + XRDP often fails inside Hyper-V Enhanced Session with errors such as:

Unit gnome-session-x11@ubuntu.target not found

This repository provides a stable XFCE-based setup that works reliably with Hyper-V Enhanced Session.

---

## Requirements

Windows host:

- Windows 11 / Windows 10
- Hyper-V enabled
- Enhanced Session Mode enabled

Check:

```powershell
Get-VMHost | fl EnableEnhancedSessionMode